    <section class="hero home-hero" id="top">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <div class="evidence">D0 · ground</div>
        <h1>Emergentism</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          The framework begins at D0. The Titans of Numbers are the boundary-frames from which the entire structure unfolds.
        </p>

        <div class="equation-strip">
          <span>⊙ = • × ○</span>
        </div>

        <div class="cta-row">
          <a href="0/" class="btn-primary">Enter /0</a>
          <a href="#spine" class="btn-ghost">View the Spine</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="chapters" id="ground">
      <article class="chapter">
        <div class="chapter-number">D0</div>
        <h2>The Ground Before the Number Line</h2>
        <p>
          Emergentism begins with three boundary-frames of being. In D1 they cast shadows as zero, infinity, and one, but the shadows do not define the glyphs.
        </p>

        <div class="titans-row" aria-label="The three Titans">
          <div class="titan-glyph">
            <div class="glyph-symbol">•</div>
            <div class="glyph-name">Zero-pole</div>
            <div class="glyph-desc">Source · absence · infinite zero · before the written numeral</div>
          </div>
          <div class="titan-glyph">
            <div class="glyph-symbol">⊙</div>
            <div class="glyph-name">Finity</div>
            <div class="glyph-desc">Unit mirror · presence · the hinge where relation becomes legible</div>
          </div>
          <div class="titan-glyph">
            <div class="glyph-symbol">○</div>
            <div class="glyph-name">Infinity-pole</div>
            <div class="glyph-desc">Horizon · totality · the unbounded surround</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="doctrine-note">
          Boundary discipline: <code>⊙ / ○ = •</code>, <code>• × ○ = ⊙</code>, and <code>⊙ / • = ○</code>
          are frame-register equations. They are not equal to <code>1/∞ = 0</code>, <code>0 × ∞ = 1</code>,
          or <code>1/0 = ∞</code>; those are D1 number-line limit shadows.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="chapters spine-section" id="spine">
      <article class="chapter">
        <div class="chapter-number">Public doctrine spine</div>
        <h2>One Page Per Dimension</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          The numbered routes are the primary public interface. Each page stands alone with one animation, scroll chapters, evidence tiers, and a Mu-limit handoff.
        </p>

        <div class="spine-grid" aria-label="Emergentism dimension pages">
          <a class="spine-card" href="0/">
            <span class="spine-number">/0 · D0</span>
            <h3>Titans of Numbers</h3>
            <p>Ground glyph register before D1 arithmetic.</p>
            <span class="spine-mode">titans</span>
          </a>
          <a class="spine-card" href="1/">
            <span class="spine-number">/1 · D1</span>
            <h3>The Special One</h3>
            <p>The logarithmic number line and one as multiplicative mirror.</p>
            <span class="spine-mode">riemann</span>
          </a>
          <a class="spine-card" href="2/">
            <span class="spine-number">/2 · D2</span>
            <h3>The Mu-Limit</h3>
            <p>The line reaches infinity, returns, and opens the plane.</p>
            <span class="spine-mode">mu-limit</span>
          </a>
          <a class="spine-card" href="3/">
            <span class="spine-number">/3 · D3</span>
            <h3>Sphere of Infinite Diameter</h3>
            <p>The plane closes into spherical balance.</p>
            <span class="spine-mode">bloch</span>
          </a>
          <a class="spine-card" href="4/">
            <span class="spine-number">/4 · D4</span>
            <h3>The Horn Torus</h3>
            <p>Rapidity, energy, and causal overlap become visible.</p>
            <span class="spine-mode">horn</span>
          </a>
          <a class="spine-card" href="5/">
            <span class="spine-number">/5 · D5</span>
            <h3>The Burrisphere</h3>
            <p>Game space, dual stereographic projections, and V/Φ tradeoff.</p>
            <span class="spine-mode">burrisphere</span>
          </a>
          <a class="spine-card" href="6/">
            <span class="spine-number">/6 · D6</span>
            <h3>Convergence and Return</h3>
            <p>The cycle closes and returns to /0.</p>
            <span class="spine-mode">convergence</span>
          </a>
